There is a new collaborative research center (SFB) "Higher Invariants -
Interations between Arithmetic Geometry and Global Analysis" at the
Department of Mathematics in Regensburg (Germany) starting April 1st.

http://www.sfb-higher-invariants.de

The CRC offers 10 Postdoc and 7 PhD Positions in various areas. We
highly welcome applications (also as guests for shorter periods).

We in particular announce the PhD Position in the project on T-Duality
(U. Bunke, T. Nikolaus). This position comes without teaching obligation
and a decent salary (3/4 of E13, roughly 1850 Euro/month after tax and
healthcare deductions).

We are seeking to hire a candidate interested in one of the following
fields:

- T-Duality and Mirror Symmetry
- Generalized complex geometry
- Homotopy theory and higher categories

For application details and any further questions, please contact
Thomas1.Nikolaus@mathematik.uni-regensburg.de



